summary: In this context, 2-ethoxy-2-methylpropane and acetonitrile are both mentioned as volatile organic compounds (VOCs) analyzed in the study of lung cancer cell lines. However, their specific relationship is not detailed, as the focus is on the release of various hydrocarbons and the decline of certain aldehydes and acetonitrile in the context of cancer cell metabolism. There is no direct interaction or functional relationship established between the two compounds.
